==Russian==
===Etymology===
Old Russian [[свекръ]], from Indo-European ''*su̯ékuro-''.  Cognate with Greek [[ἑκυρός]], Latin [[socer]], Old English [[sweor|swēor]].

===Noun===
'''свёкор''' (svjókor) {{m}}

# a woman’s [[father-in-law]] ''(husband’s father only)''

